    "is_accepted" : true,
    "score" : 313,
    "last_activity_date" : 1513459037,
    "last_edit_date" : 1513459037,
    "creation_date" : 1427228442,
    "answer_id" : 29242123,
    "question_id" : 29241640,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>This really needs to be added to the documentation, which is why I filed <a href=\"https://code.google.com/p/android/issues/detail?id=82711\" rel=\"noreferrer\">an issue about it</a> a few months ago...</p>\n\n<p>You need some 32-bit binaries, and you have a 64-bit OS version (apparently). Try:</p>\n\n<pre><code>sudo apt-get install lib32z1 lib32ncurses5 lib32bz2-1.0 lib32stdc++6\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>That worked for me on Ubuntu 14.10.</p>\n\n<p><strong>UPDATE 2017-12-16</strong>: The details will vary by Linux distro and version. So for example, <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/31088492/115145\">this answer</a> covers newer Ubuntu versions.</p>\n"
  }, {
