      "user_id" : 2295484,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 90,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/BAohf.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Krishnadas PC",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2295484/krishnadas-pc"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 13,
    "last_activity_date" : 1436279912,
    "creation_date" : 1436279912,
    "answer_id" : 31271734,
    "question_id" : 29241640,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>For Ubuntu, you can try:</p>\n\n<pre><code>sudo apt-get install lib32z1 lib32ncurses5 lib32bz2-1.0 lib32stdc++6\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>For Cent OS/RHEL try :</p>\n\n<pre><code>sudo yum install zlib.i686 ncurses-libs.i686 bzip2-libs.i686 \n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Then, re-install the Android Studio and get success.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3732732,
      "reputation" : 986,
      "user_id" : 3104569,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 83,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/iIcsF.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "kartikmaji",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3104569/kartikmaji"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 6,
    "last_activity_date" : 1445513488,
    "creation_date" : 1445513488,
    "answer_id" : 33279983,
    "question_id" : 29241640,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>This worked for me on Ubuntu 15.04</p>\n\n<p><code>sudo aptitude install lib32stdc++6</code></p>\n\n<p>Firstly, I installed aptitude, which helps in installing other dependencies too.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4107999,
      "reputation" : 158,
      "user_id" : 3371410,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/HxUYk.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "vjs3",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3371410/vjs3"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1451175999,
    "creation_date" : 1451175999,
    "answer_id" : 34476547,
    "question_id" : 29241640,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>In case of <strong>lubuntu</strong> 14.04 use</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>sudo apt-get install lib32z1 lib32ncurses5 lib32bz2-1.0 lib32stdc++6</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>P.S-no need to restart the system.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 5862765,
      "reputation" : 793,
      "user_id" : 4617869,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 0,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/NGvM8.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "connelblaze",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4617869/connelblaze"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 5,
    "last_activity_date" : 1462549889,
    "last_edit_date" : 1462549889,
    "creation_date" : 1462543256,
    "answer_id" : 37074357,
    "question_id" : 29241640,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>if you do this: \n<code>sudo apt-get install lib32z1 lib32ncurses5 lib32bz2-1.0 lib32stdc++6</code>. \nYou may get this error:</p>\n\n<pre><code>E: Unable to locate package lib32bz2-1.0\n\nE: Couldn't find any package by glob 'lib32bz2-1.0'\n\nE: Couldn't find any package by regex 'lib32bz2-1.0'\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>So i suggest just doing this:</p>\n\n<p><code>sudo apt-get install lib32stdc++6</code></p>\n\n<p>And also, the AOSP should look for how while installing Android-Studio, that is installed too.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2117463,
      "reputation" : 123,
      "user_id" : 2423729,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ca9680beaad866525d6ee73887f6973d?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "vivi",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2423729/vivi"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 10,
    "last_activity_date" : 1463085734,
    "creation_date" : 1463085734,
    "answer_id" : 37197045,
    "question_id" : 29241640,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Here's what you need to do to fix the issue on Arch Linux :</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li><p>Enable the <code>multilib</code> repository on your system if you have not already done so by uncommenting the <code>[multilib]</code> section in <code>/etc/pacman.conf</code> :</p>\n\n<pre><code>[multilib]\nInclude = /etc/pacman.d/mirrorlist\n</code></pre></li>\n<li><p>Update pacman :</p>\n\n<pre><code># pacman -Suy\n</code></pre></li>\n<li><p>Install the 32 bit version of libstdc++5 :</p>\n\n<pre><code># pacman -S lib32-libstdc++5\n</code></pre></li>\n</ol>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 7370319,
      "reputation" : 2035,
      "user_id" : 5610686,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 56,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d1c019b04f819493cc743b0bf37e4542?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Pritish Joshi",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5610686/pritish-joshi"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1472532498,
    "creation_date" : 1472532498,
    "answer_id" : 39218943,
    "question_id" : 29241640,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>This is what worked for me </p>\n\n<p>When I tried the Accepted ans my Android Studio hangs on start-up</p>\n\n<p>This is the link </p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p><a href=\"http://tools.android.com/tech-docs/linux-32-bit-libraries\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://tools.android.com/tech-docs/linux-32-bit-libraries</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>and This is the Command </p>\n\n<pre><code>$ sudo apt-get install libc6:i386 libncurses5:i386 libstdc++6:i386 lib32z1\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1685084,
      "reputation" : 1633,
      "user_id" : 1548557,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/dh45O.jpg?s=256",
